option as well.

00:07:43.445 --> 00:07:44.870
If I open up this drop menu,

00:07:44.870 --> 00:07:46.880
you can see we have
three different options.

00:07:46.880 --> 00:07:49.250
We have lazy, eager, and auto.

00:07:49.250 --> 00:07:51.890
What do they mean when
it said too lazy,

00:07:51.890 --> 00:07:56.405
the browser will load this
image once it comes into view.

00:07:56.405 --> 00:07:58.430
So e.g. if I scroll down here,

00:07:58.430 --> 00:08:00.920
we have different
images and these images

00:08:00.920 --> 00:08:03.830
won't be loaded until
they come into view.

00:08:03.830 --> 00:08:07.085
So when we scroll
down right here,

00:08:07.085 --> 00:08:09.365
the browser will
load these images.

00:08:09.365 --> 00:08:09.830
This way.

00:08:09.830 --> 00:08:12.290
We can make sure that
our webpage loads

00:08:12.290 --> 00:08:15.155
very fast and it's
very good for SEO.

00:08:15.155 --> 00:08:17.645
But we can override
this setting as well.

00:08:17.645 --> 00:08:18.995
I can select this image,

00:08:18.995 --> 00:08:21.530
I can go to the image
settings and from here

00:08:21.530 --> 00:08:24.290
I can set it too eager
loads with page.

00:08:24.290 --> 00:08:28.355
So if I select this option
when the page loads,

00:08:28.355 --> 00:08:30.650
this image will be
loaded as well.

00:08:30.650 --> 00:08:32.839
Therefore, it's
more time consuming

00:08:32.839 --> 00:08:35.255
for the browser to
load our web page.

00:08:35.255 --> 00:08:37.055
You can also set it to auto,

00:08:37.055 --> 00:08:40.490
and it will behave based on
the browsers preferences.

00:08:40.490 --> 00:08:44.270
My suggestion is that you
should always set it too lazy.

00:08:44.270 --> 00:08:46.145
As I mentioned
before, by default,

00:08:46.145 --> 00:08:48.695
all your images
are set too lazy.

00:08:48.695 --> 00:08:51.020
But I'm going to
mention one more thing.

